        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 2:43PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 242 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Morrice, or near Perry, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Flint, Hartland, Fenton, Howell, Durand, Fowlerville, Perry, Burton,
Swartz Creek, Linden, Cohoctah, Morrice, Byron, Bancroft, Gaines, Oak
Grove, Lake Fenton, Argentine, Rankin, and Conway Township.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
